entries.femaleVariant: 'Ey, you. Sittin' in the wrong spot.
Uhhh... Thisss... This isn't a bar?
It is. But it's our bar.
Get up. Let's take a walk.
'Ey, back off. Ain't your biz here.
What, you deaf? You lookin' to get beat? 'Cause that's what's about to happen.
Go ahead. Make my day.
Don't even start with me.
Mama Welles doesn't like fights.
Fine. Do what you want.
[pl_pl][INVISIBLE LINE, IGNORE]
Just try, gonk. C'mon. Let's see what you got.
Really think you're fast enough with that blade? Really?
Really? Mh, wonder what Mama Welles would say – what she'd do when she sees you two gonks fuckin' up her joint.
entries.maleVariant: Really? Wonder what Mama Welles would say – what she'd do when she sees you two gonks fuckin' up her joint.

entries.femaleVariant: Know what? Fine. Not my biz, not my corpo.
entries.maleVariant: You know what? Fine. Not my biz, not my corpo.

entries.femaleVariant: 'Ey, wait! Know this punk. Fought fire with our boys – y'know, back when Gustavo took that hit.
But... What... What just happened?
Well. Just got real fuckin' interesting.
A'ight, c'mon, Pedro. Not worth it. Don't work out.
'Cause I know you got scratch.
'Cause I knew you were in trouble.
'Cause you look like you got some eds on you.
'Cause you woulda caught a beatin'. Or worse.
Nah. Just don't want to go home.
Keep talking.
Meddling in someone's marriage? No thanks.
Run me through it.
Marital strife? Sorry, not my line of work.
You sure? Damn... Well, if you change your mind, lemme know.
It's about my wife, right? Name's Cynthia. She's cheating – damn sure of it. Only question is, who with.
Sure, I'm in.
Where do I find your wife?
How do you know she's cheating?
Why do you wanna know?
Gonna have to keep tabs on your wife, follow her around town. Where'd she be now?
Sure she's cheatin' on you?
She works nearby, I'll give you the address. Knowing her, she'll be on a smoke break. Smokes like a goddamn tire fire.
Wait, um... Today, she was wearing a – pink jacket... and, uh... Hmm... She had a blue purse, I think.
Let's start with the fact that she always stays late after work. I know she's lying. Called her office one night, she wasn't even there.
Used to be easy to check these things – but with today's tech? There's a way around every test now.
Why you wanna know who she's with? What's the point?
What's the point?! What kind of gonk question is that?!
<mothertongue l="mex" m="Mierda" b="" a=". Looked like a fat wallet, too."/>
Eh – not the only collar in town, man.
An' stay out! If ya know what's good for you!
Really? Ain't deaf or blind, an' all I see is two gonks tryna rob a stumblin' suit.
Choom – fuck off. Or I implant my blade in your ribs.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="chica" b="Oh, so we got your permission, " a="? Great. Now get the fuck out."/>
entries.maleVariant: <mothertongue l="mex" m="hombre" b="Oh, so we got your permission, " a="? Great. Now get the fuck out."/>

entries.femaleVariant: Well, come on, choom. Fresh air'll do you some good.
My bet's she'd whip out her shotgun, blast your heads off.
Way I see it, be a smokin' hole in your chest before your neurons even light up.
But hey, nothin' like a little experiment, right?
<mothertongue l="mex" m="¡Carajo!" b="Yo, fuck you! " a=" Fuckin' punk."/>
Landed in a little trouble. Cleaned up now.
Goddamn, sorry, I... I think I've had a little too much... Fuck! What a night...
Why...? Why'd you help me?
I see... Nothing for free. Not in this goddamn city. Not in this goddamn life.
Here. All I got. The rest... bartender got the rest.
This fuckin' town, these people...? Just here, mindin' my own biz... If it weren't for you, I... ugh...
Here. For your trouble. The rest, uh... bartender got the rest.
Ten years married, y'know? Ten years an' suddenly I am not good enough. Nooo, she has to go get some side action.
Anyhow, since you brought up money... you wouldn't be lookin' for a gig, would ya, V? Pay's solid.
Could let it eat away at me, or I could get someone like you. Ain't no more than an evening's work.
Eh, not for me after all.
Can't say I'm interested. Sorry.
Simple one. Answer it.
I want to look him in the eyes – ask him how it feels, fucking some other guy's wife, breaking up a happy marriage.
Like half this city.
Colorful.
Always liked dressing up. Get a woman something nice for her birthday, anniversary... And what do you get in return?
No, no, no, no, wait – eh, to hell with it.
You're my hero, V. Means a lot to me.
OK, fine. I'm in.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="cabrones" b="Ey, leave him alone, " a="!"/>
V! Go teach these assholes how to behave in my bar!
Circling him like sharks on the scent o' fresh corpo blood... Coulda ended badly if you hadn't've stepped in, V.
How about we drink to you, then? On the house.
Sure.
No thanks.
Not this time. But thanks.
Won't say no to a free drink.
Don't drink on the clock, eh? I get it, respect that.
To good fortune and prosperity!
Thanks, V. Really outdid yourself.
You heard what Pepe said. Take a fuckin' walk.
Yeah, well, not all heroes wear capes.
Long day?
Could say that again. I'm on a double, no break.
Workin' overtime to make an extra buck?
'Sides that? Well, we got a kid together, right? Doesn't even look like me. Different hair, different eyes, all of it!
So? You gonna help me out after all?
Not interested.
Lay off him.
